  <text>
    <p>
If a matrix has integer entries, will the entries stay integers when you row-reduce it? </p>
    <p>
      <optionresponse>
        <optioninput options="('Yes','Not necessarily')" correct="Not necessarily"/>
      </optionresponse>
    </p>
    <p>
      <solution>
        <font color="blue">Answer: </font>
        <font color="blue">
          <p>
No. For example, to put </p>
          <table id="a0000000022" class="equation" width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="7" style="table-layout:auto">
            <tr>
              <td class="equation" style="width:80%;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;border-style:hidden">[mathjax]\left[ \begin{array}{ccc} 2 &amp;  0 &amp;  1 \\ 0 &amp;  1 &amp;  1 \end{array} \right].[/mathjax]</td>
              <td class="eqnnum" style="width:20%;vertical-align:middle;text-align:left;border-style:hidden"/>
            </tr>
          </table>
          <p>
 into RREF, we have to multiply Row 1 by [mathjaxinline]\frac{1}{2}[/mathjaxinline], which will create a non-integer entry.  </p>
        </font>
      </solution>
    </p>
  </text>
</problem>
